<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3660</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04T17:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8075. Ascertain and cable as soon as possible attitude of British
                            Government towards status of British officers and crews of British or
                            foreign armed merchant vessels who have been captured and interned by
                            Germans. Does British Government acknowledge German right of capture and
                            regard these men as prisoners of war? Does Government or employers pay
                            them salaries or relief, and do salaries date from time of original
                            capture on high sea or date of landing as prisoners? What amounts are
                            paid respectively to officers and men? Report fully any arrangements
                            made in this connection.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>